  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Heat a pot with a lid with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once the butter has melted, add your <strong>nigella seeds</strong> and<strong> basmati rice</strong> and stir to fully coat the grains</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/663.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/663.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/663.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/663.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/663.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> to the pot and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving – this is your <strong>nigella rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/663.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/663.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/663.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/663.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/663.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 10 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/663.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/663.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/663.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/663.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/663.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks (save some leaves for garnish!)</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Trim, then chop your <strong>green beans</strong> in half</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1624351301264-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1624351301264-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1624351301264-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1624351301264-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1624351301264-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[375ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>sultanas</strong> and <strong>mango chutney</strong> to the stock and stir to combine – this is your <strong>mango stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/663.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/663.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/663.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/663.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/663.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>chicken breast strips</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> to the softened onion cook for a further 2 min</p><p>Increase the heat to high and add the <strong>chopped chicken</strong>, <strong>ground turmeric</strong>, <strong>curry powder </strong>and a good grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> to the pan and cook for a 4-5 min or until lightly browned and everything is coated in spice</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1624351334536-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1624351334536-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1624351334536-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1624351334536-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1624351334536-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>mango</strong> <strong>stock</strong> and <strong>chopped green beans </strong>cook for a further 6-8 min until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the stock has reduced by half</p><p>Remove the pan from the heat and stir in your <strong>natural yoghurt</strong> and <strong>chopped coriander</strong></p><p>Taste and season with more<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> if needed – this is your <strong>coronation chicken curry</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1624351338297-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1624351338297-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1624351338297-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1624351338297-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1624351338297-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Fluff the <strong>nigella rice</strong> with a fork</p><p>Serve the <strong>coronation chicken curry</strong> with the <strong>nigella rice</strong> and garnish with the <strong>reserved coriander leaves</strong></p><p>Sprinkle over your<strong> flaked almonds</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
